  <brief_title>Fentanyl Transdermal Matrix Patch ZR-02-01 to Treat Chronic, Moderate to Severe Osteoarthritis (OA) Pain</brief_title>
  <official_title>Double-Blind, Parallel, Randomized, Placebo-Controlled 12-Week Efficacy and Safety Assessment of ZR-02-01 in the Treatment of Chronic, Moderate to Severe Osteoarthritis (OA) Pain</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>ZARS Pharma Inc.</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>ZARS Pharma Inc.</source>
  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate the effectiveness of the Matrix Fentanyl Patch
      ZR-02-01 in providing pain relief.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This study will evaluate the analgesic efficacy of the matrix fentanyl patch. The study will
      be conducted in non-opioid tolerant patients with moderate to severe osteoarthritis (OA)
      pain. This patient population was chosen in anticipation that the patients are otherwise
      healthy adults being treated with NSAIDs (Nonsteroidal Anti-inflammatory Drugs) or
      acetaminophen or who have received intermittent opioid analgesic treatment.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
